{
  "texts": [
    "Maintaining the system's normal operation at the least possible cost of energy consumption, such as keeping the overall temperature stable at a low-range, can be viewed as an optimal control problem.",
    "A potential solution to this problem is through data-driven models with physical priors, which combines a structured model derived from the connection relationship and functions of physical equipment and data-driven methods to build a dynamic control framework.",
    "By monitoring and adjusting the parameter configuration of each module of the system in real-time, this framework can achieve the optimal operating status and energy consumption cost.",
    "RC has the potential to play a crucial role in this approach.",
    "Opportunities."
  ]
}